Cook the rice: Place the @brown rice{1.5%cup} and a @salt{large pinch} in a large #pot with enough water to cover by 3 inches. Bring to a boil and cook for about ~{25%minutes}, until tender. Drain when finished (like pasta).

Wash and dry all produce. Core, seed, and thinly slice the @yellow bell peppers{2}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and mince the @ginger{2%thumb}. Mince or grate the @garlic{4%cloves}. Finely chop the @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Trim the @sugar snap peas{12%ounce}. Halve 1 @lime{2}; cut the other lime into wedges.

Prep the pork: Cut the @pork tenderloin{24%ounce} into 1-inch cubes and toss in a medium #bowl with the @cornstarch{2%tablespoon} and a large pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Working in batches, add the pork to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{3-4%minutes}, until browned. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Heat another large drizzle of oil in the same pan over medium-high heat. Add the onion, garlic, and ginger to the pan. Cook, tossing for ~{2-3%minutes}, until softened. Add the bell pepper to the pan and cook for another ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the sugar snap peas to the pan and cook for another ~{2-3%minutes}, until crisp-tender. Stir in the pork, @hoisin sauce{2%jar}, cilantro, and the juice of 1 lime. Toss for ~{1%minute}, until heated through. Serve the hoisin pork stir-fry on a bed of brown rice, with lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!